comments:
The first part of the word was always 'sme' or 'sma', I had trouble remembering if the word uses 'e' or 'a', but it wasn't crucial as I used the second part of the word to remember them. The second parts were similar to real English words: pyg - pig, pids - pits, byn - bin etc. so I used that to help me memorise them. 
I found this study rather easy and very interesting
